Logical questions

    1 Below is presented a series of numbers: 2 – 3 - 6 – 7 – 8 – 14 - 15 – 30

        1.a Which number does not belong to above series?

        1.b Please specify what will be the next 2 numbers of the above series?

    2 How many months have 28 days?

    3 Name four days of a week which starts with “T”?

**************************************************************************************
    1.1 The pattern is: +1,×2, +1, ×2, +1, and ×2  (8 does not belong;)
    1.2 31 - 62
    2 Every month has 28 days.
    3 Tuesday, Thursday, Today, Tomorrow